    "John Trapp": "And put their heads in baskets. ] Apposite ad culpam Achab, saith A Lapide: this was suitable to Ahab\u2019s sin. He had sent for baskets of grapes out of Naboth\u2019s vineyard at Jezreel; and now the heads of his sons are brought thither in baskets. Oh, doleful burden!\nVer.\n7. And put their heads in baskets.] Apposite ad culpam Achab, saith A Lapide: this was suitable to Ahab\u2019s sin. He had sent for baskets of grapes out of Naboth\u2019s vineyard at Jezreel; and now the heads of his sons are brought thither in baskets. Oh, doleful burden!\nVer.\n7. And the Philistines came and dwelt in them. ] But before they were well warm in these their new nests, David `[char_David_Rut_4]` unroosted and dislodged them \"The triumphing of the wicked is but short.\" { #Job 20:5 }\nVer.\n7. And the Philistines came and dwelt in them.] But before they were well warm in these their new nests, David `[char_David_Rut_4]` unroosted and dislodged them \"The triumphing of the wicked is but short.\" {#Job 20:5}\nVer."
